    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for any of 32 species of web-footed aquatic mammals that live chiefly in cold seas and whose body shape, round at the middle and tapered at the ends, is adapted to swift and graceful swimming. There are two types of animals often called by this term: the earless, or true, seals (family Phocidae); and the eared seals (family Otariidae), which comprise the sea lions and fur seals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
